{
  "stem": "8892.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, it was so naive and so stupid to realize that if they're in here, why wouldn't they be in the next town?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, what happened when you were all gathered when your sister came back, and you were all gathered in the synagogue, where did you go from there?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then when we were gathered, all the Jews gathered with the family, children, mother, father-- everybody-- sick ones, old ones, all of them in a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we stayed there all night, and then in a synagogue they would divide like, I don't know, maybe with a curtain or something.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And even when you're dressed-- so when we're going and we know that we have to be there, this was I think on a Saturday-- on a Saturday, and we stayed all day Saturday in the synagogue and slept on a floor.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, we'd get dressed, as many clothes as we can, so I put on all my underwear, layers of slips, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think two, three skirts-- anything, but I thought it was good-- and my winter coat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it's already almost spring.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the same with my sister and my mother, and we packed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And nobody had that many suitcases.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they made bundles.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This is my clothing, and that was my sister, my brother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And all the Jews are in a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In a synagogue, they take the men, strip them to naked.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That's already with the Hungarian police and a German solider directing and being there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And at one point, I think my sister was a little bit further away from me, and they get to me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My mother is stripped and standing there so weak and so sickly.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I'm a young girl, and I'm sick.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
